:: Rejection target: a commutativity-style orientation `join(x, y) -> join(y, x)`
:: keeps the resolved term-AST node count unchanged, so it violates the strict
:: size decrease required by the default simplification order. Same-size
:: orientation is explicitly not accepted
:: (doc/spec/en/17.clusters_and_registrations.md, section 17.6.4, rule 3).

definition
  let x, y be set;
  func JoinDef: join(x, y) -> set equals x;
end;

registration
  let x, y be set;

  reduce JoinComm: join(x, y) to join(y, x);
  reducibility proof thus thesis; end;
end;
